J/A+A/561/A127   ynogkm: code for calculating time-like geodesics  (Yang+, 2014)
================================================================================
ynogkm: A new public code for calculating time-like geodesics in the
Kerr-Newmann spacetime.
    Yang X.-L., Wang J.-C.
   <Astron. Astrophys. 561, A127 (2014)>
   =2014A&A...561A.127Y
================================================================================
ADC_Keywords: Models ; Accretion
Keywords: accretion, accretion disks - black hole physics -
          relativistic processes - methods: numerical

Description:
    Here we present the source file for a new public code named ynogkm,
    aim on calculating the time-like geodesics in a Kerr-Newmann spacetime
    fast. In the code the four Boyer-Lindquis coordinates and proper time
    are expressed as functions of a parameter p semi-analytically, i.e.,
    r(p), {mu}(p), {phi}(p), t(p), and {sigma}(p), by using the Weiers-
    trass' and Jacobi's elliptic functions and integrals. All of the
    ellip- tic integrals are computed by Carlson's elliptic integral
    method, which guarantees the fast speed of the code.The source Fortran
    file ynogkm.f90 contains three modules: constants, rootfind,
    ellfunction, and blcoordinates.

